ref=\"http://militiatoday.com/groups/butler-county-pennsylvania/\">Butler County, Pennsylvania</a>','Welcome to the Butler County, PA MilitiaToday group!','http://militiatoday.com/members/militatoday/',1,0,'2014-12-09 22:07:04',0,0,0,0),(12,1,'bbpress','bbp_topic_create','<a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/members/militatoday/\">MilitiaToday</a> started the topic <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/topic/butler-board-sets-timeline-for-consolidation-decision/\">Butler Board Sets Timeline For Consolidation Decision</a> in the forum <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/forum/counties/butler-county-pennsylvania/local-news/\">Local News</a>','The Butler School Board has set a timeline for the process of making a decision about possibly consolidating.\n\nAt their meeting Monday night, it was determined that the board will choose a plan to undergo final consideration in January, hold a public hearing on that plan in February, and vote to implement the plan in May.\n\nA Facilities Master Plan Presentation will be given on Monday, December 15th at 7 p.m. at the Intermediate High School auditorium in which more information will be provided about the three most likely plans.\n\nHowever, no decision will be made at next week\'s meeting.','http://militiatoday.com/topic/butler-board-sets-timeline-for-consolidation-decision/',192,184,'2014-12-09 22:52:56',0,0,0,0),(13,1,'bbpress','bbp_topic_create','<a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/members/militatoday/\">MilitiaToday</a> started the topic <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/topic/bc3-announces-new-scholarship/\">BC3 Announces New Scholarship</a> in the forum <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/forum/counties/butler-county-pennsylvania/local-news/\">Local News</a>','<a href=\"http://www.ask4direct.com/images/info/956313.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.ask4direct.com/images/info/956313.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"153\" height=\"180\" /></a>The BC3 Education Foundation has teamed up with C.W. Howard Insurance to establish a new scholarship.\n\nThe C.W. Howard Insurance Family Scholarship will be awarded for the first time during the 2015-2016 school year to a 2015 graduate of the Cardinal Wuerl North Catholic High School who is attending Butler County Community College. The monetary amount was not specified.\n\nThe scholarship is meant to inspire a new generation of community leaders in Butler County.\n\nFor more information about the Butler County Community College Scholarship Program, visit www.bc3.edu.','http://militiatoday.com/topic/bc3-announces-new-scholarship/',193,184,'2014-12-09 22:55:24',0,0,0,0),(14,1,'bbpress','bbp_topic_create','<a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/members/militatoday/\">MilitiaToday</a> started the topic <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/topic/roof-error-could-cost-county-50000/\">Roof Error Could Cost County $50,000</a> in the forum <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/forum/counties/butler-county-pennsylvania/local-news/\">Local News</a>','[caption id=\"\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\" class=\" \"]<img id=\"__wp-temp-img-id\" src=\"http://www.ask4direct.com/images/info/956482.jpg\" alt=\"Butler County Pennsylvania\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /> Butler County Pennsylvania[/caption]\n\n<a>A problem in the construction of the roof on the new downtown Butler County office building could cost as much as $50,000.\n\nThe Butler County commissioners discussed the error during Monday\'s agenda-setting meeting.\n\nOfficials say a \'discrepancy in the drawings\' led to the roof being installed without a slope to drain rainwater. The problem is being corrected by installing insulation.\n\nBoard chairman Bill McCarrier said he is concerned with the problem but noted the $11 million project is still coming in under budget because of some changes to the scope of work.\n\nThe building will sit on South Washington Street next to the Butler County Government Center and house county human services.</a>','http://militiatoday.com/topic/roof-error-could-cost-county-50000/',195,184,'2014-12-09 22:59:25',0,0,0,0),(15,1,'bbpress','bbp_topic_create','<a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/members/militatoday/\">MilitiaToday</a> started the topic <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/topic/roof-error-could-cost-county-50000/\">Roof Error Could Cost County $50,000</a> in the forum <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/forum/counties/butler-county-pennsylvania/local-news/\">Local News</a>','[caption id=\"\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\" class=\" \"]<img id=\"__wp-temp-img-id\" src=\"http://www.ask4direct.com/images/info/956482.jpg\" alt=\"Butler County Pennsylvania\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /> Butler County Pennsylvania[/caption]\r\n\r\nA problem in the construction of the roof on the new downtown Butler County office building could cost as much as $50,000.\r\n\r\nThe Butler County commissioners discussed the error during Monday\'s agenda-setting meeting.\r\n\r\nOfficials say a \'discrepancy in the drawings\' led to the roof being installed without a slope to drain rainwater. The problem is being corrected by installing insulation.\r\n\r\nBoard chairman Bill McCarrier said he is concerned with the problem but noted the $11 million project is still coming in under budget because of some changes to the scope of work.\r\n\r\nThe building will sit on South Washington Street next to the Butler County Government Center and house county human services.','http://militiatoday.com/topic/roof-error-could-cost-county-50000/',195,184,'2014-12-09 22:59:25',0,0,0,0),(16,1,'bbpress','bbp_topic_create','<a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/members/militatoday/\">MilitiaToday</a> started the topic <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/topic/roof-error-could-cost-county-50000/\">Roof Error Could Cost County $50,000</a> in the forum <a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/forum/counties/butler-county-pennsylvania/local-news/\">Local News</a>','<img id=\"__wp-temp-img-id\" src=\"http://www.ask4direct.com/images/info/956482.jpg\" alt=\"Butler County, Pennsylvania\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" />\n\nA problem in the construction of the roof on the new downtown Butler County office building could cost as much as $50,000.\n\nThe Butler County commissioners discussed the error during Monday\'s agenda-setting meeting.\n\nOfficials say a \'discrepancy in the drawings\' led to the roof being installed without a slope to drain rainwater. The problem is being corrected by installing insulation.\n\nBoard chairman Bill McCarrier said he is concerned with the problem but noted the $11 million project is still coming in under budget because of some changes to the scope of work.\n\nThe building will sit on South Washington Street next to the Butler County Government Center and house county human services.','http://militiatoday.com/topic/roof-error-could-cost-county-50000/',195,184,'2014-12-09 22:59:25',0,0,0,0),(17,1,'blogs','new_blog_post','<a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/members/militatoday/\" title=\"MilitiaToday\">MilitiaToday</a> created a new listing, Chester John Suski','Chester Suski\'s friends and family knew he was a strong believer in the merits of hard work. “He worked until he was 90,” said his son, James Suski of Murrysville. Chester John “C.J.” Suski of Jefferson Hills, [&hellip;]','http://militiatoday.com/?p=202',1,202,'2014-12-09 23:36:20',0,0,0,0),(18,1,'blogs','new_blog_post','<a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/members/militatoday/\" title=\"MilitiaToday\">MilitiaToday</a> created a new listing, Carl E. Janusek','<a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/?p=203\"><img src=\"http://militiatoday.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/sdfghsdfg-217x300.jpg\" width=\"72\" height=\"100\" alt=\"Thumbnail\" class=\"align-left thumbnail\" /></a><a href=\"http://militiatoday.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/sdfghsdfg.jpg\">\r\n\r\nIf they hailed from Western Pennsylvania or recorded an album in Pittsburgh from the 1940s through the \'60s, it is likely “Mon Valley Musicologist” Carl Janusek knew as much about the artists as anyone. “If [&hellip;]</a>','http://mi