ment\nstate: \" The Right to Keep and Bear Arms shall not be\nInfringed?\" Or, does it say :  “The Privilege of the\nPeople to Keep and Bear Arms shall not be Infringed\nunless a Constitutionally corrupt Gov’t. creates\nreasons to remove the Privilege?\"\n\nThe answer is obviously, \" The Right of the People to\nKeep and Bear Arms shall not be Infringed.\"\n\nNow, if they have already shown not only a willingness\nto, but have already VIOLATED the Bill of Rights by\nreducing them to \"Privileges\" subject to the fancies\nof the Republi-Crats and they whom they select as\nSupreme Court justices for LIFE; do you yet see any\ndanger to them now saying that Rights are now \"\nprivileges\" that can be Legislatively limited in\nviolation of the Preamble to the Bill of Rights?\nAt what point is the line drawn? According unto\nSCOTUS in their opinion...\n\n\"Second, whereas the word \"violent\" or \"violence\"\nstanding alone \"connotes a substantial degree of\nforce,\" id., at 140, that is not true of \"domestic\nviolence,\" which is a term of \"art\" encompassing acts\nthat one might not characterize as \"violent\" in a non-\ndomestic context...\"\n\nThis statement means ANYTHING! The question is\nnow, \" How long will it be before \"for public safety,\"\nsimply arguing with a police officer gets you the same\nthing as arguing with a spouse? The \"door\" has been\nopened, and your \"Rights\" as enumerated are subject\nto legislative manipulation.\n\nThe question now is, \"Are you happy with liberal\njudges now \"interpreting\" when you\'ve lost your\n\"privilege\" as a result of an error? Or are you\nprovoked that they have just told you that you HAVE\nNO SECOND AMENDMENT RIGHT?\n\nBefore its ratification, it was insisted upon that a\nPreamble be written thereto. (Please notice that the\n“Bill” is singular-not plural!)\n\nThe Preamble states;\n\n“THE Conventions of a number of the States having at\nthe time of their adopting the Constitution, expressed\na desire, in order